notesStmt.note: Title from caption title (f. 1r); spine title: Los Pastoreillos (Gillet's title notation; Zacour-Hirsch).
Incipit of play: Le, Le, Le, Le / de decirlo acabaré / ... (f. 2r).
Many stains and smudges. Many leaves slightly frayed or torn at the edges.

msContents.summary: Nativity play divided into three "jornadas," the birth of Our Lord and the Life of Our Lady (with some stage directions).

supportDesc.extent: 115 leaves : 215 x 152 mm. bound to 226 x 167 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, iii (modern) + 115 + iii (modern); [1-115 (105-115 blank)], modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

origin.p: Written in Spain in the 18th century.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Joseph E. Gillet; purchased from his estate, 1958.
